  "rollout_plan_displayname": "Will ship enabled for all users",
  "motivation": "The 'letter-spacing' and 'word-spacing' properties currently only accept fixed length values (e.g. px, em), which are inflexible in responsive designs. When font sizes or container dimensions change, this fixed spacing can become disproportionate, forcing developers to write complex media queries or use JavaScript to maintain readable text. Introducing percentage values allows spacing to be defined relative to font-intrinsic metrics. This enables both letter and word spacing to scale proportionally with the font, simplifying the creation of robust and visually consistent typography across all devices without extra code.",
